79  "Valid log levels are:\n"

86 cmd_line::cmd_line()
87  : test_mode(false), output_redirected(false)
88 {
89 }
90 
91 cmd_line::cmd_line(void (*notification_callback)(void *, int32_t, uint64_t, uint16_t, uint16_t, uint16_t, uint32_t, void *),
92  void (*log_callback)(void *, int32_t, const char *, int32_t),
93  bool test_mode, char * interface, int32_t log_level)
94  : test_mode(test_mode), output_redirected(false)
95 {
96  cout_buf = std::cout.rdbuf();
97  current_end_station = 0;
98 
99  // Start non-zero so as not to be confused with commands without notification
100  notification_id = 1;
101 
102  cmd_line_commands_init();
103 
104  netif = avdecc_lib::create_net_interface();
105  controller_obj = avdecc_lib::create_controller(netif, notification_callback, log_callback, log_level);
106  controller_obj->apply_end_station_capabilities_filters(avdecc_lib::ENTITY_CAPABILITIES_GPTP_SUPPORTED |
107  avdecc_lib::ENTITY_CAPABILITIES_AEM_SUPPORTED,
108  0, 0);
109 
110  sys = avdecc_lib::create_system(avdecc_lib::system::LAYER2_MULTITHREADED_CALLBACK, netif, controller_obj);
111  atomic_cout << "AVDECC Controller version: " << controller_obj->get_version() << std::endl;
112  print_interfaces_and_select(interface);
113  sys->process_start();
114 }
115 
116 cmd_line::~cmd_line()
117 {
118  sys->process_close();
119  sys->destroy();
120  controller_obj->destroy();
121  netif->destroy();
122  ofstream_ref.close();
123 }

127  return &commands;
128 }

130 avdecc_lib::controller * cmd_line::get_controller() const
131 {
132  return controller_obj;
133 }
134 
135 bool cmd_line::handle(std::vector<std::string> & args)
136 {
137  std::queue<std::string, std::deque<std::string>> args_queue(std::deque<std::string>(args.begin(), args.end()));
138  bool done = false;
139  bool ok = commands.run_command(this, args_queue, done);
140  if (!ok)
141  {
142  printf("Invalid command\n");
143  commands.print_help_all("", 1);
144  }
145  return done;
146 }
147 
148 int cmd_line::print_interfaces_and_select(char * interface)
149 {
150  int interface_num = -1;
151 
152  for (uint32_t i = 1; i < netif->devs_count() + 1; i++)
153  {
154  char * dev_desc = netif->get_dev_desc_by_index(i - 1);
155  if (!interface)
156  {
157  printf("%d (%s)\n", i, dev_desc);
158  }
159  else
160  {
161  if (strcmp(dev_desc, interface) == 0)
162  {
163  interface_num = i;
164  break;
165  }
166  }
167  }
168 
169  if (!interface)
170  {
171  atomic_cout << "Enter the interface number (1-" << std::dec << netif->devs_count() << "): ";
172  std::cin >> interface_num;
173  }
174 
175  netif->select_interface_by_num(interface_num);
176 
177  return 0;
178 }
179 
180 int cmd_line::get_current_end_station(avdecc_lib::end_station ** end_station) const
181 {
182  if (current_end_station >= controller_obj->get_end_station_count())
183  {
184  atomic_cout << "No End Stations available" << std::endl;
185  *end_station = NULL;
186  return 1;
187  }
188 
189  *end_station = controller_obj->get_end_station_by_index(current_end_station);
190  return 0;
191 }
192 
193 int cmd_line::get_current_entity_and_descriptor(avdecc_lib::end_station * end_station,
194  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor ** entity, avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor ** configuration)
195 {
196  *entity = NULL;
197  *configuration = NULL;
198 
199  uint16_t current_entity = end_station->get_current_entity_index();
200  if (current_entity >= end_station->entity_desc_count())
201  {
202  atomic_cout << "Current entity not available" << std::endl;
203  return 1;
204  }
205 
206  *entity = end_station->get_entity_desc_by_index(current_entity);
207 
208  uint16_t current_config = end_station->get_current_config_index();
209  if (current_config >= (*entity)->config_desc_count())
210  {
211  atomic_cout << "Current configuration not available" << std::endl;
212  return 1;
213  }
214 
215  *configuration = (*entity)->get_config_desc_by_index(current_config);
216 
217  return 0;
218 }
219 
220 int cmd_line::get_current_end_station_entity_and_descriptor(avdecc_lib::end_station ** end_station,
221  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor ** entity, avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor ** configuration)
222 {
223  if (get_current_end_station(end_station))
224  return 1;
225 
226  if (get_current_entity_and_descriptor(*end_station, entity, configuration))
227  {
228  atomic_cout << "Current End Station not fully enumerated" << std::endl;
229  return 1;
230  }
231  return 0;
232 }

234 void cmd_line::cmd_line_commands_init()
235 {
236  // Create the commands. Each command can have multiple sub-commands and/or multiple formats.
237  // Each format is what will ultimately call back into the cmd_line to perform the processing
238  // once the arguments have matched.
239 
240  // help
241  cli_command * help_cmd = new cli_command();
242  commands.add_sub_command("help", help_cmd);
243 
244  cli_command_format * help_one_fmt = new cli_command_format(
245  "Display details of specified command.",
246  &cmd_line::cmd_help_one);
247  help_one_fmt->add_argument(new cli_argument_string(this, "cmd", "the command for which to show details", "", 1, UINT_MAX));
248  help_cmd->add_format(help_one_fmt);
249 
250  cli_command_format * help_all_fmt = new cli_command_format(
251  "Display a list of valid commands.\n"
252  "Use \"help -a\" to display a complete list of commands",
253  &cmd_line::cmd_help_all);
254  help_cmd->add_format(help_all_fmt);
255 
256  // version
257  cli_command * version_cmd = new cli_command();
258  commands.add_sub_command("version", version_cmd);
259 
260  cli_command_format * version_format = new cli_command_format(
261  "Display the current AVDECC Controller build release version.",
262  &cmd_line::cmd_version);
263  version_cmd->add_format(version_format);
264 
265  // list
266  cli_command * list_cmd = new cli_command();
267  commands.add_sub_command("list", list_cmd);
268 
269  cli_command_format * list_fmt = new cli_command_format(
270  "Display a table with information about each End Station.",
271  &cmd_line::cmd_list);
272  list_cmd->add_format(list_fmt);
273 
274  // select
275  cli_command * select_cmd = new cli_command("To see a list of valid End Stations, enter \"list\" command.");
276  commands.add_sub_command("select", select_cmd);
277 
278  cli_command_format * select_fmt = new cli_command_format(
279  "Change the setting of End Station, entity, and configuration.",
280  &cmd_line::cmd_select);
281  select_fmt->add_argument(new cli_argument_end_station(this, "e_s", END_STATION_HELP));
282  select_fmt->add_argument(new cli_argument_int(this, "e_i", "the entity index"));
283  select_fmt->add_argument(new cli_argument_int(this, "c_i", "the configuration index"));
284  select_cmd->add_format(select_fmt);
285 
286  cli_command_format * show_select_fmt = new cli_command_format(
287  "Display the current End Station, Entity, and Configuration setting.",
288  &cmd_line::cmd_show_select);
289  select_cmd->add_format(show_select_fmt);
290 
291  // audio mappings
292  cli_command * audio_mappings = new cli_command();
293  commands.add_sub_command("audio_mappings", audio_mappings);
294 
295  // remove audio mappings
296  cli_command * remove_audio_mappings_cmd = new cli_command();
297  audio_mappings->add_sub_command("remove", remove_audio_mappings_cmd);
298  cli_command_format * remove_audio_mappings_fmt = new cli_command_format(
299  "Send a REMOVE_AUDIO_MAPPINGS command to remove the queued mapping entries\n"
300  "from the dynamic mapping between the Audio Clusters and Input/Output Streams\n",
301  &cmd_line::cmd_remove_audio_mappings);
302  remove_audio_mappings_fmt->add_argument(new cli_argument_string(this, "d_t", "the descriptor type",
303  "Valid descriptor types are STREAM_PORT_INPUT and STREAM_PORT_OUTPUT."));
304  remove_audio_mappings_fmt->add_argument(new cli_argument_int(this, "d_i", "the descriptor index",
305  "To see a list of valid descriptor types and corresponding indexes, enter\n"
306  "\"view all\" command."));
307  remove_audio_mappings_cmd->add_format(remove_audio_mappings_fmt);
308 
309  // store pending audio mapping
310  cli_command * store_pending_audio_mapping_cmd = new cli_command();
311  audio_mappings->add_sub_command("store_pending", store_pending_audio_mapping_cmd);
312 
313  cli_command_format * store_pending_audio_mapping_fmt = new cli_command_format(
314  "Send an ADD_PENDING_AUDIO_MAPPING command to add mapping entries to a local queue.\n"
315  "for adding or removal\n",
316  &cmd_line::cmd_store_pending_audio_mapping);
317  store_pending_audio_mapping_fmt->add_argument(new cli_argument_string(this, "d_t", "the descriptor type",
318  "Valid descriptor types are STREAM_PORT_INPUT and STREAM_PORT_OUTPUT."));
319  store_pending_audio_mapping_fmt->add_argument(new cli_argument_int(this, "d_i", "the descriptor index",
320  "To see a list of valid descriptor types and corresponding indexes, enter\n"
321  "\"view all\" command."));
322 
323  store_pending_audio_mapping_fmt->add_argument(new cli_argument_int(this, "s_i", "the stream index."));
324  store_pending_audio_mapping_fmt->add_argument(new cli_argument_int(this, "s_c", "the stream channel"));
325  store_pending_audio_mapping_fmt->add_argument(new cli_argument_int(this, "c_o", "the cluster offset."));
326  store_pending_audio_mapping_fmt->add_argument(new cli_argument_int(this, "c_c", "the cluster channel."));

328  store_pending_audio_mapping_cmd->add_format(store_pending_audio_mapping_fmt);

334  cli_command_format * get_pending_audio_mappings_fmt = new cli_command_format(
335  "Send an GET_PENDING_AUDIO_MAPPINGS command to read queued entries.",

338  "Valid descriptor types are STREAM_PORT_INPUT and STREAM_PORT_OUTPUT."));

340  "To see a list of valid descriptor types and corresponding indexes, enter\n"
341  "\"view all\" command."));
342  get_pending_audio_mappings_cmd->add_format(get_pending_audio_mappings_fmt);
343 
344  // clear pending audio mappings

346  audio_mappings->add_sub_command("clear_pending", clear_pending_audio_mappings_cmd);
347 
348  cli_command_format * clear_pending_audio_mappings_fmt = new cli_command_format(
349  "Send an CLEAR_PENDING_AUDIO_MAPPINGS command to clear queued entries.",

367  "Valid descriptor types are STREAM_PORT_INPUT and STREAM_PORT_OUTPUT."));

1045 int cmd_line::cmd_help_one(int total_matched, std::vector<cli_argument *> args)
1046 {
1047  std::vector<std::string> tmp = args[0]->get_all_value_str();
1048  if (tmp[0] == "-a")
1049  {
1050  commands.print_help_all("", UINT_MAX);
1051  }
1052  else
1053  {
1054  std::string prefix;
1055  std::queue<std::string, std::deque<std::string>> args_queue(std::deque<std::string>(tmp.begin(), tmp.end()));
1056  const cli_command * cmd = commands.get_sub_command(args_queue, prefix);
1057  if (cmd)
1058  {
1059  cmd->print_help_details(prefix);
1060  }
1061  else
1062  {
1063  printf("Could not find command to print help for. Matched up to '%s'\n", prefix.c_str());
1064  }
1065  }
1066  return 0;
1067 }

1080 int cmd_line::cmd_list(int total_matched, std::vector<cli_argument *> args)
1081 {
1082  atomic_cout << "\n"
1083  << "End Station"
1084  << " | "
1085  << "Name" << std::setw(21) << " | "
1086  << "Entity ID" << std::setw(12) << " | "
1087  << "Firmware Version"
1088  << " | "
1089  << "MAC" << std::endl;
1090  atomic_cout << std::string(100, '-') << std::endl;
1091 
1092  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < controller_obj->get_end_station_count(); i++)
1093  {
1094  avdecc_lib::end_station * end_station = controller_obj->get_end_station_by_index(i);
1095 
1096  if (end_station)
1097  {
1098  uint64_t end_station_entity_id = end_station->entity_id();
1099  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor_response * ent_desc_resp = NULL;
1100  if (end_station->entity_desc_count())
1101  {
1102  uint16_t current_entity = end_station->get_current_entity_index();
1103  ent_desc_resp = end_station->get_entity_desc_by_index(current_entity)->get_entity_response();
1104  }
1105  const char * end_station_name = "";
1106  const char * fw_ver = "";
1107  if (ent_desc_resp)
1108  {
1109  end_station_name = (const char *)ent_desc_resp->entity_name();
1110  fw_ver = (const char *)ent_desc_resp->firmware_version();
1111  }
1112  uint64_t end_station_mac = end_station->mac();
1113  atomic_cout << (std::stringstream() << end_station->get_connection_status()
1114  << std::setw(10) << std::dec << std::setfill(' ') << i << " | "
1115  << std::setw(20) << std::hex << std::setfill(' ') << (ent_desc_resp ? end_station_name : "UNKNOWN") << " | 0x"
1116  << std::setw(16) << std::hex << std::setfill('0') << end_station_entity_id << " | "
1117  << std::setw(16) << std::hex << std::setfill(' ') << (ent_desc_resp ? fw_ver : "UNKNOWN") << " | "
1118  << std::setw(12) << std::hex << std::setfill('0') << end_station_mac)
1119  .rdbuf()
1120  << std::endl;
1121  delete (ent_desc_resp);
1122  }
1123  }
1124 
1125  atomic_cout << "\nC - End Station Connected." << std::endl;
1126  atomic_cout << "D - End Station Disconnected." << std::endl;
1127 
1128  return 0;
1129 }

1131 int cmd_line::cmd_view_media_clock(int total_matched, std::vector<cli_argument *> args)
1132 {
1133  uint8_t * desc_obj_name;
1134  uint16_t desc_type_value = 0;
1135  uint16_t desc_index = 0;
1136  bool is_clock_sync_source_set = false;
1137 
1138  atomic_cout << "\n"
1139  << "End Station"
1140  << " " << std::setw(20) << "Descriptor Name"
1141  << " "
1142  << std::setw(18) << "Descriptor Type"
1143  << " " << std::setw(18) << "Descriptor Index" << std::endl;
1144  atomic_cout << "------------------------------------------------------------------------------" << std::endl;
1145 
1146  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < controller_obj->get_end_station_count(); i++)
1147  {
1148  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * configuration = controller_obj->get_current_config_desc(i, false);
1149 
1150  if (configuration)
1151  {
1152  for (unsigned int j = 0; j < configuration->stream_input_desc_count(); j++)
1153  {
1154  avdecc_lib::stream_input_descriptor * stream_input_desc = configuration->get_stream_input_desc_by_index(j);
1155  if (stream_input_desc)
1156  {
1157  avdecc_lib::stream_input_descriptor_response * stream_input_resp_ref = stream_input_desc->get_stream_input_response();
1158  is_clock_sync_source_set = stream_input_resp_ref->stream_flags_clock_sync_source();
1159  if (is_clock_sync_source_set)
1160  {
1161 
1162  desc_obj_name = stream_input_resp_ref->object_name();
1163  desc_type_value = stream_input_desc->descriptor_type();
1164  desc_index = stream_input_desc->descriptor_index();
1165 
1166  atomic_cout << std::setw(8) << i << std::setw(5) << "" << std::setw(20) << desc_obj_name
1167  << " " << std::setw(18) << avdecc_lib::utility::aem_desc_value_to_name(desc_type_value)
1168  << " " << std::setw(16) << std::dec << desc_index << std::endl;
1169  }
1170  delete (stream_input_resp_ref);
1171  }
1172  }
1173 
1174  for (unsigned int j = 0; j < configuration->stream_output_desc_count(); j++)
1175  {
1176  avdecc_lib::stream_output_descriptor * stream_output_desc = configuration->get_stream_output_desc_by_index(j);
1177  if (stream_output_desc)
1178  {
1179  avdecc_lib::stream_output_descriptor_response * stream_output_resp_ref = stream_output_desc->get_stream_output_response();
1180  is_clock_sync_source_set = stream_output_resp_ref->stream_flags_clock_sync_source();
1181  if (is_clock_sync_source_set)
1182  {
1183  desc_obj_name = stream_output_resp_ref->object_name();
1184  desc_type_value = stream_output_desc->descriptor_type();
1185  desc_index = stream_output_desc->descriptor_index();
1186 
1187  atomic_cout << std::setw(8) << i << std::setw(5) << "" << std::setw(20) << desc_obj_name
1188  << " " << std::setw(18) << std::hex << avdecc_lib::utility::aem_desc_value_to_name(desc_type_value)
1189  << " " << std::setw(16) << std::dec << desc_index << std::endl;
1190  }
1191  delete (stream_output_resp_ref);
1192  }
1193  }
1194  }
1195  }
1196 
1197  return 0;
1198 }

1223 int cmd_line::cmd_select(int total_matched, std::vector<cli_argument *> args)

1231 
1232 int cmd_line::do_select(uint32_t new_end_station, uint16_t new_entity, uint16_t new_config)
1233 {
1234  if (is_setting_valid(new_end_station, new_entity, new_config)) // Check if the new setting is valid
1235  {
1236  avdecc_lib::end_station * end_station = controller_obj->get_end_station_by_index(new_end_station);
1237  uint16_t current_entity = end_station->get_current_entity_index();
1238  uint16_t current_config = end_station->get_current_config_index();
1239  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor_response * entity_desc_resp = end_station->get_entity_desc_by_index(current_entity)->get_entity_response();
1240 
1241  uint8_t * end_station_name = entity_desc_resp->entity_name();
1242 
1243  if ((current_end_station == new_end_station) && (current_entity == new_entity) && (current_config == new_config))
1244  {
1245  atomic_cout << "Same setting" << std::endl;
1246  atomic_cout << "\tEnd Station Index: " << std::dec << current_end_station << " (" << end_station_name << ")" << std::endl;
1247  atomic_cout << "\tEntity Index: " << std::dec << current_entity << std::endl;
1248  atomic_cout << "\tConfiguration Index: " << std::dec << current_config << std::endl;
1249  }
1250  else
1251  {
1252  current_end_station = new_end_station;
1253  end_station->set_current_entity_index(new_entity);
1254  end_station->set_current_config_index(new_config);
1255  atomic_cout << "New setting" << std::endl;
1256  atomic_cout << "\tEnd Station Index: " << std::dec << current_end_station << " (" << end_station_name << ")" << std::endl;
1257  atomic_cout << "\tEntity Index: " << std::dec << current_entity << std::endl;
1258  atomic_cout << "\tConfiguration Index: " << std::dec << current_config << std::endl;
1259  }
1260  delete entity_desc_resp;
1261  }
1262  else
1263  {
1264  atomic_cout << "Invalid new setting" << std::endl;
1265  }
1266 
1267  return 0;
1268 }
1269 
1270 int cmd_line::cmd_log_level(int total_matched, std::vector<cli_argument *> args)
1271 {
1272  uint32_t new_log_level = args[0]->get_value_int();
1273  if (new_log_level < avdecc_lib::TOTAL_NUM_OF_LOGGING_LEVELS)
1274  {
1275  controller_obj->set_logging_level(new_log_level);
1276  }
1277  else
1278  {
1279  atomic_cout << "Invalid new log level" << std::endl;
1280  }
1281 
1282  return 0;
1283 }

1285 int cmd_line::cmd_log(int total_matched, std::vector<cli_argument *> args)
1286 {
1287  std::string file = log_path + "/" + args[0]->get_value_str() + ".txt";
1288  try
1289  {
1290  ofstream_ref.open(file);
1291  ofstream_ref.good();
1292  std::cout.rdbuf(ofstream_ref.rdbuf());
1293  output_redirected = true;
1294  atomic_cout << "Re-directing logging to " << file << std::endl;
1295  }
1296  catch (std::ofstream::failure e)
1297  {
1298  atomic_cout << "ofstream exception" << std::endl;
1299  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1300  }
1301  return 0;
1302 }

1313 void cmd_line::print_desc_type_index_name_row(avdecc_lib::descriptor_base & desc,
1314  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor & configuration,
1315  size_t localized_description,
1316  const uint8_t * object_name,
1317  avdecc_lib::locale_descriptor & locale)
1318 {
1319  //const uint8_t localized_string_max_index = 7;
1320 
1321  atomic_cout << std::setw(20) << avdecc_lib::utility::aem_desc_value_to_name(desc.descriptor_type())
1322  << " " << std::setw(16) << std::dec << desc.descriptor_index();
1323 
1324  if ((desc.descriptor_type() == avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_STREAM_PORT_INPUT) ||
1325  (desc.descriptor_type() == avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_STREAM_PORT_OUTPUT) ||
1326  (desc.descriptor_type() == avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_AUDIO_MAP))
1327  {
1328  atomic_cout << " " << std::endl;
1329  }
1330  else
1331  {
1332  if (object_name && object_name[0] != '\0')
1333  {
1334  atomic_cout << " " << std::setw(20) << std::hex << object_name << std::endl;
1335  }
1336  else
1337  {
1338  size_t string_desc_index;
1339  size_t string_index;
1340  int ret = configuration.get_strings_desc_string_by_reference(localized_description,
1341  string_desc_index, string_index);
1342  if (ret == 0)
1343  {
1344  avdecc_lib::strings_descriptor * desc = configuration.get_strings_desc_by_index(string_desc_index);
1345  avdecc_lib::strings_descriptor_response * strings_resp_ref = desc->get_strings_response();
1346  atomic_cout << " " << std::setw(20) << std::hex << strings_resp_ref->get_string_by_index(string_index) << std::endl;
1347  delete strings_resp_ref;
1348  }
1349  else
1350  {
1351  atomic_cout << " " << std::endl;
1352  }
1353  }
1354  }
1355 }
1356 
1357 int cmd_line::cmd_view_all(int total_matched, std::vector<cli_argument *> args)
1358 {
1359  uint8_t * obj_name = NULL;
1360 
1361  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < controller_obj->get_end_station_count(); i++)
1362  {
1363  avdecc_lib::end_station * end_station = controller_obj->get_end_station_by_index(i);
1364  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor * entity;
1365  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * configuration;
1366  if (get_current_entity_and_descriptor(end_station, &entity, &configuration))
1367  continue;
1368 
1369  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor_response * entity_resp = entity->get_entity_response();
1370 
1371  obj_name = entity_resp->entity_name();
1372  atomic_cout << "\nEnd Station: " << i << " (" << obj_name << ")" << std::endl;
1373  atomic_cout << std::setw(20) << "Descriptor Type"
1374  << " " << std::setw(16)
1375  << "Descriptor Index"
1376  << " " << std::setw(20) << "Descriptor Name" << std::endl;
1377  atomic_cout << "------------------------------------------------------------------------------" << std::endl;
1378  delete entity_resp;
1379 
1380  if ((configuration->locale_desc_count() == 0) || (configuration->strings_desc_count() == 0))
1381  continue;
1382 
1383  avdecc_lib::locale_descriptor * locale = configuration->get_locale_desc_by_index(0);
1384 
1385  switch (0)
1386  {
1387  case avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_ENTITY:
1388  {
1389  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor_response * entity_resp = entity->get_entity_response();
1390  atomic_cout << std::setw(20) << std::hex << avdecc_lib::utility::aem_desc_value_to_name(entity->descriptor_type())
1391  << " " << std::setw(16) << std::dec << entity->descriptor_index()
1392  << " " << std::setw(20) << std::hex << entity_resp->entity_name() << std::endl;
1393  delete entity_resp;
1394  }
1395 
1396  case avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_CONFIGURATION:
1397  {
1398  atomic_cout << std::setw(20) << avdecc_lib::utility::aem_desc_value_to_name(configuration->descriptor_type())
1399  << " " << std::setw(16) << std::dec << configuration->descriptor_index()
1400  << " " << std::setw(20) << std::hex << configuration->object_name() << std::endl;
1401  atomic_cout << "\nTop Level Descriptors" << std::endl;
1402  }
1403 
1404  case avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_AUDIO_UNIT:
1405  for (unsigned int j = 0; j < configuration->audio_unit_desc_count(); j++)
1406  {
1407  avdecc_lib::audio_unit_descriptor * audio_unit_desc_ref = configuration->get_audio_unit_desc_by_index(j);
1408  avdecc_lib::audio_unit_descriptor_response * audio_unit_resp_ref = audio_unit_desc_ref->get_audio_unit_response();
1409  print_desc_type_index_name_row(*audio_unit_desc_ref,
1410  *configuration,
1411  audio_unit_resp_ref->localized_description(),
1412  audio_unit_resp_ref->object_name(),
1413  *locale);
1414  delete audio_unit_resp_ref;
1415  }
1416 
1417  case avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_STREAM_INPUT:
1418  for (unsigned int j = 0; j < configuration->stream_input_desc_count(); j++)
1419  {
1420  avdecc_lib::stream_input_descriptor * stream_input_desc_ref = configuration->get_stream_input_desc_by_index(j);
1421  avdecc_lib::stream_input_descriptor_response * stream_input_resp_ref = stream_input_desc_ref->get_stream_input_response();
1422  print_desc_type_index_name_row(*stream_input_desc_ref,
1423  *configuration,
1424  stream_input_resp_ref->localized_description(),
1425  stream_input_resp_ref->object_name(),
1426  *locale);
1427  delete stream_input_resp_ref;
1428  }
1429 
1430  case avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_STREAM_OUTPUT:
1431  for (unsigned int j = 0; j < configuration->stream_output_desc_count(); j++)
1432  {
1433  avdecc_lib::stream_output_descriptor * stream_output_desc_ref = configuration->get_stream_output_desc_by_index(j);
1434  avdecc_lib::stream_output_descriptor_response * stream_output_resp_ref = stream_output_desc_ref->get_stream_output_response();
1435  print_desc_type_index_name_row(*stream_output_desc_ref,
1436  *configuration,
1437  stream_output_resp_ref->localized_description(),
1438  stream_output_resp_ref->object_name(),
1439  *locale);
1440  delete stream_output_resp_ref;
1441  }
1442 
1443  case avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_JACK_INPUT:
1444  for (unsigned int j = 0; j < configuration->jack_input_desc_count(); j++)
1445  {
1446  avdecc_lib::jack_input_descriptor * jack_input_desc_ref = configuration->get_jack_input_desc_by_index(j);
1447  avdecc_lib::jack_input_descriptor_response * jack_input_resp_ref = jack_input_desc_ref->get_jack_input_response();
1448  print_desc_type_index_name_row(*jack_input_desc_ref,
1449  *configuration,
1450  jack_input_resp_ref->localized_description(),
1451  jack_input_resp_ref->object_name(),
1452  *locale);

1891 
1892 int cmd_line::do_view_descriptor(std::string desc_name, uint16_t desc_index)
1893 {
1894  avdecc_lib::end_station * end_station;
1895  if (get_current_end_station(&end_station))
1896  return 0;
1897 
1898  uint16_t desc_type_value = avdecc_lib::utility::aem_desc_name_to_value(desc_name.c_str());
1899 
1900  atomic_cout << "\ndescriptor_type: " << avdecc_lib::utility::aem_desc_value_to_name(desc_type_value);
1901  atomic_cout << "\ndescriptor_index: " << std::dec << desc_index;
1902 
1903  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor * entity;
1904  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * configuration;
1905  get_current_entity_and_descriptor(end_station, &entity, &configuration);
1906 
1907  // test field output
1908  if (desc_type_value == avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_EXTERNAL_PORT_INPUT)
1909  {
1910  avdecc_lib::descriptor_base * desc = configuration->get_external_port_input_desc_by_index(desc_index)->get_external_port_input_response();
1911  uint32_t v = 0;
1912 
1913  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < desc->field_count(); i++)
1914  {
1915  avdecc_lib::descriptor_field * f = desc->field(i);
1916  switch (f->get_type())
1917  {
1918  case avdecc_lib::descriptor_field::TYPE_CHAR:
1919  atomic_cout << "\n"
1920  << f->get_name() << " = " << f->get_char();
1921  break;
1922  case avdecc_lib::descriptor_field::TYPE_UINT16:
1923  atomic_cout << "\n"
1924  << f->get_name() << " = " << f->get_uint16();
1925  break;
1926  case avdecc_lib::descriptor_field::TYPE_UINT32:
1927  atomic_cout << "\n"
1928  << f->get_name() << " = " << f->get_uint32();
1929  break;
1930  // Don't have to handle these separately here, but internal to the library they have different types.
1931  case avdecc_lib::descriptor_field::TYPE_FLAGS16:
1932  case avdecc_lib::descriptor_field::TYPE_FLAGS32:
1933  v = f->get_flags();
1934  atomic_cout << "\nFlags " << f->get_name() << " = 0x" << std::setfill('0') << std::setw(8) << std::hex << v;
1935  for (unsigned int j = 0; j < f->get_flags_count(); j++)
1936  {
1937  uint32_t the_bit;
1938  avdecc_lib::descriptor_field_flags * fl = f->get_flag_by_index(j);
1939 
1940  the_bit = ((v & fl->get_flag_mask()) != 0);
1941  atomic_cout << "\n\t" << std::setw(32) << fl->get_flag_name() << " = " << the_bit << " (mask is 0x" << std::setfill('0') << std::setw(8) << std::hex << fl->get_flag_mask() << ")";
1942  }
1943  break;
1944  default:
1945  atomic_cout << "\nUNHANDLED FIELD TYPE";
1946  }
1947  }
1948  delete desc;
1949  return 0;
1950  }
1951

1953  {
1954  case avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_ENTITY:

1957  {
1958  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor_response * entity_desc_resp = entity->get_entity_response();
1959  atomic_cout << "\nentity_id = 0x" << std::hex << entity_desc_resp->entity_id();
1960  atomic_cout << "\nentity_model_id = " << std::dec << entity_desc_resp->entity_model_id();

2533 int cmd_line::cmd_read_descriptor(int total_matched, std::vector<cli_argument *> args)
2534 {
2535  std::string desc_name = args[0]->get_value_str();
2536  uint16_t desc_index = args[1]->get_value_int();
2537 
2538  avdecc_lib::end_station * end_station;
2539  if (get_current_end_station(&end_station))
2540  return 0;
2541 
2542  uint16_t desc_type_value = avdecc_lib::utility::aem_desc_name_to_value(desc_name.c_str());
2543  intptr_t cmd_notification_id = 0;
2544 
2545  if (desc_type_value < avdecc_lib::TOTAL_NUM_OF_AEM_DESCS)
2546  {
2547  cmd_notification_id = get_next_notification_id();
2548  sys->set_wait_for_next_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id);
2549  end_station->send_read_desc_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id, desc_type_value, desc_index);
2550  sys->get_last_resp_status();
2551  }
2552  else
2553  {
2554  atomic_cout << "cmd_read_descriptor error" << std::endl;
2555  }
2556 
2557  return 0;
2558 }
2559 
2560 int cmd_line::cmd_connect(int total_matched, std::vector<cli_argument *> args)
2561 {
2562  uint8_t * outstream_end_station_name;
2563  uint8_t * instream_end_station_name;
2564  const char * format;
2565  size_t stream_input_desc_count = 0;
2566  size_t stream_output_desc_count = 0;
2567  uint64_t end_station_mac;
2568 
2569  atomic_cout << "\n"
2570  << "End Station" << std::setw(28) << ""
2571  << "Instream" << std::setw(19) << ""
2572  << "Stream Format" << std::endl;
2573  atomic_cout << "---------------------------------------------------------------------------------" << std::endl;
2574 
2575  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < controller_obj->get_end_station_count(); i++)
2576  {
2577  avdecc_lib::end_station * end_station = controller_obj->get_end_station_by_index(i);
2578  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor * entity;
2579  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * configuration;
2580  if (get_current_entity_and_descriptor(end_station, &entity, &configuration))
2581  continue;
2582 
2583  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor_response * entity_desc_resp = entity->get_entity_response();
2584  end_station_mac = end_station->mac();
2585  instream_end_station_name = entity_desc_resp->entity_name();
2586  stream_input_desc_count = configuration->stream_input_desc_count();
2587 
2588  for (uint32_t j = 0; j < stream_input_desc_count; j++)
2589  {
2590  avdecc_lib::stream_input_descriptor * input_descriptor = configuration->get_stream_input_desc_by_index(j);
2591  avdecc_lib::stream_input_descriptor_response * stream_input_resp_ref = input_descriptor->get_stream_input_response();
2592  format = stream_input_resp_ref->current_format_name();
2593  uint8_t * desc_desc_name = stream_input_resp_ref->object_name();
2594  uint8_t * input_stream_name;
2595  size_t string_desc_index;
2596  size_t string_index;
2597  if (desc_desc_name[0] == '\0')
2598  {
2599  int ret = configuration->get_strings_desc_string_by_reference(stream_input_resp_ref->localized_description(),
2600  string_desc_index, string_index);
2601  if (ret == 0)
2602  {
2603  avdecc_lib::strings_descriptor * desc = configuration->get_strings_desc_by_index(string_desc_index);
2604  avdecc_lib::strings_descriptor_response * strings_resp_ref = desc->get_strings_response();
2605  input_stream_name = strings_resp_ref->get_string_by_index(string_index);
2606 
2607  atomic_cout << std::setw(5) << i << std::setw(25) << instream_end_station_name
2608  << avdecc_lib::utility::end_station_mac_to_string(end_station_mac) << " "
2609  << std::setw(3) << j << std::setw(19) << input_stream_name << " "
2610  << std::setw(14) << format << std::endl;
2611 
2612  delete strings_resp_ref;
2613  }
2614  }
2615  else
2616  {
2617  input_stream_name = desc_desc_name;
2618 
2619  atomic_cout << std::setw(5) << i << std::setw(25) << instream_end_station_name
2620  << avdecc_lib::utility::end_station_mac_to_string(end_station_mac) << " "
2621  << std::setw(3) << j << std::setw(19) << input_stream_name << " "
2622  << std::setw(14) << format << std::endl;
2623  }
2624  delete stream_input_resp_ref;
2625  }
2626  delete entity_desc_resp;
2627  }
2628 
2629  atomic_cout << "\n"
2630  << "End Station" << std::setw(28) << ""
2631  << "Outstream" << std::setw(15) << ""
2632  << "Stream Format" << std::endl;
2633  atomic_cout << "---------------------------------------------------------------------------------" << std::endl;
2634 
2635  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < controller_obj->get_end_station_count(); i++)
2636  {
2637  avdecc_lib::end_station * end_station = controller_obj->get_end_station_by_index(i);
2638  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor * entity;
2639  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * configuration;
2640  if (get_current_entity_and_descriptor(end_station, &entity, &configuration))
2641  continue;
2642 
2643  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor_response * entity_desc_resp = entity->get_entity_response();
2644  end_station_mac = end_station->mac();
2645  outstream_end_station_name = entity_desc_resp->entity_name();
2646  stream_output_desc_count = configuration->stream_output_desc_count();
2647 
2648  for (uint32_t j = 0; j < stream_output_desc_count; j++)
2649  {
2650  avdecc_lib::stream_output_descriptor * output_descriptor = configuration->get_stream_output_desc_by_index(j);
2651  avdecc_lib::stream_output_descriptor_response * stream_output_resp_ref = output_descriptor->get_stream_output_response();
2652  format = stream_output_resp_ref->current_format_name();
2653  uint8_t * src_desc_name = stream_output_resp_ref->object_name();
2654  uint8_t * output_stream_name;
2655  size_t string_desc_index;
2656  size_t string_index;
2657  if (src_desc_name[0] == '\0')
2658  {
2659  int ret = configuration->get_strings_desc_string_by_reference(stream_output_resp_ref->localized_description(),
2660  string_desc_index, string_index);
2661  if (ret == 0)
2662  {
2663  avdecc_lib::strings_descriptor * desc = configuration->get_strings_desc_by_index(string_desc_index);
2664  avdecc_lib::strings_descriptor_response * strings_resp_ref = desc->get_strings_response();
2665  output_stream_name = strings_resp_ref->get_string_by_index(string_index);
2666 
2667  atomic_cout << std::setw(5) << i << std::setw(25) << instream_end_station_name
2668  << avdecc_lib::utility::end_station_mac_to_string(end_station_mac) << " "
2669  << std::setw(3) << j << std::setw(19) << output_stream_name
2670  << " " << std::setw(14) << format << std::endl;
2671 
2672  delete strings_resp_ref;
2673  }
2674  }
2675  else
2676  {
2677  output_stream_name = src_desc_name;
2678 
2679  atomic_cout << std::setw(5) << i << std::setw(25) << instream_end_station_name
2680  << avdecc_lib::utility::end_station_mac_to_string(end_station_mac) << " "
2681  << std::setw(3) << j << std::setw(19) << output_stream_name
2682  << " " << std::setw(14) << format << std::endl;
2683  }
2684  delete stream_output_resp_ref;
2685  }
2686  delete entity_desc_resp;
2687  }
2688 
2689  return 0;
2690 }

2692 int cmd_line::cmd_connect_dst(int total_matched, std::vector<cli_argument *> args)
2693 {

2695  uint16_t instream_desc_index = args[1]->get_value_int();
2696 
2697  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * configuration = controller_obj->get_current_config_desc(instream_end_station_index, false);

2700  (instream_desc_index < configuration->stream_input_desc_count()));

2717  {

2754 int cmd_line::cmd_connect_rx(int total_matched, std::vector<cli_argument *> args)
2755 {
2756  uint32_t outstream_end_station_index = args[0]->get_value_uint();
2757  uint16_t outstream_desc_index = args[1]->get_value_int();
2758  uint32_t instream_end_station_index = args[2]->get_value_uint();
2759  uint16_t instream_desc_index = args[3]->get_value_int();
2760  const std::vector<std::string> & flags = args[4]->get_all_value_str();
2761 
2762  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * in_descriptor = controller_obj->get_current_config_desc(instream_end_station_index, false);
2763  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * out_descriptor = controller_obj->get_current_config_desc(outstream_end_station_index, false);
2764  bool is_valid = (in_descriptor && out_descriptor &&
2765  (test_mode || (instream_end_station_index != outstream_end_station_index)) &&
2766  (instream_end_station_index < controller_obj->get_end_station_count()) &&
2767  (outstream_end_station_index < controller_obj->get_end_station_count()) &&
2768  (instream_desc_index < in_descriptor->stream_input_desc_count()) &&
2769  (outstream_desc_index < out_descriptor->stream_output_desc_count()));
2770 
2771  if (is_valid)
2772  {
2773  uint16_t connection_flags = 0;
2774  for (std::vector<std::string>::const_iterator it = flags.begin(); it != flags.end(); ++it)
2775  {
2776  const std::string flag = *it;
2777  if (flag == "class_b")
2778  {
2779  connection_flags |= 0x1;
2780  }
2781  else if (flag == "fast_connect")
2782  {
2783  connection_flags |= 0x2;
2784  }
2785  else if (flag == "saved_state")
2786  {
2787  connection_flags |= 0x4;
2788  }
2789  else if (flag == "streaming_wait")
2790  {
2791  connection_flags |= 0x8;
2792  }
2793  else if (flag == "supports_encrypted")
2794  {
2795  connection_flags |= 0x8;
2796  }
2797  else if (flag == "encrypted_pdu")
2798  {
2799  connection_flags |= 0x10;
2800  }
2801  else if (flag == "talker_failed")
2802  {
2803  connection_flags |= 0x10;
2804  }
2805  else if (flag != "")
2806  {
2807  atomic_cout << "\nInvalid Flag" << std::endl;
2808  return 0;
2809  }
2810  }
2811 
2812  intptr_t cmd_notification_id = 0;
2813  uint64_t talker_entity_id;
2814  bool check_stream_format;
2815 
2816  cmd_notification_id = get_next_notification_id();
2817  sys->set_wait_for_next_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id);
2818  avdecc_lib::stream_input_descriptor * instream = in_descriptor->get_stream_input_desc_by_index(instream_desc_index);
2819  avdecc_lib::stream_input_descriptor_response * stream_input_resp_ref = instream->get_stream_input_response();
2820  avdecc_lib::stream_output_descriptor * outstream = out_descriptor->get_stream_output_desc_by_index(outstream_desc_index);
2821  avdecc_lib::stream_output_descriptor_response * stream_output_resp_ref = outstream->get_stream_output_response();
2822  check_stream_format = (strcmp(stream_input_resp_ref->current_format_name(), stream_output_resp_ref->current_format_name()) == 0);
2823  if (!check_stream_format)
2824  {
2825  atomic_cout << "\n[WARNING] Stream formats do not match. \nInstream has stream format: " << stream_input_resp_ref->current_format_name()
2826  << "\nOutstream has stream format: " << stream_output_resp_ref->current_format_name() << std::endl;
2827  }
2828 
2829  avdecc_lib::end_station * outstream_end_station = controller_obj->get_end_station_by_index(outstream_end_station_index);
2830  uint16_t outstream_current_entity = outstream_end_station->get_current_entity_index();
2831  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor_response * entity_resp_ref = outstream_end_station->get_entity_desc_by_index(outstream_current_entity)->get_entity_response();
2832  talker_entity_id = entity_resp_ref->entity_id();
2833  delete (entity_resp_ref);
2834  instream->send_connect_rx_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id, talker_entity_id, outstream_desc_index, connection_flags);
2835  sys->get_last_resp_status();
2836 
2837  delete (stream_input_resp_ref);
2838  }
2839  else
2840  {
2841  atomic_cout << "Invalid ACMP Connection" << std::endl;
2842  }
2843 
2844  return 0;
2845 }
2846

2848 {
2849  uint32_t outstream_end_station_index = args[0]->get_value_uint();
2850  uint16_t outstream_desc_index = args[1]->get_value_int();

2855  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * out_descriptor = controller_obj->get_current_config_desc(outstream_end_station_index, false);
2856  bool is_valid = (in_descriptor && out_descriptor &&
2857  (test_mode || (instream_end_station_index != outstream_end_station_index)) &&
2858  (instream_end_station_index < controller_obj->get_end_station_count()) &&

2860  (instream_desc_index < in_descriptor->stream_input_desc_count()) &&

2873  uint16_t current_entity = outstream_end_station->get_current_entity_index();

2875  talker_entity_id = entity_resp_ref->entity_id();
2876  delete (entity_resp_ref);

2879  sys->get_last_resp_status();
2880  }
2881  else
2882  {
2883  atomic_cout << "Invalid ACMP Disconnection" << std::endl;
2884  }
2885 
2886  return 0;

2889 int cmd_line::cmd_show_connections(int total_matched, std::vector<cli_argument *> args)
2890 {
2891  // Use the same notification ID for all the read commands
2892  intptr_t cmd_notification_id = get_next_notification_id();
2893 
2894  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < controller_obj->get_end_station_count(); i++)
2895  {
2896  avdecc_lib::end_station * end_station = controller_obj->get_end_station_by_index(i);
2897  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor * entity;
2898  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * configuration;
2899  if (get_current_entity_and_descriptor(end_station, &entity, &configuration))
2900  continue;
2901 
2902  size_t stream_input_desc_count = configuration->stream_input_desc_count();
2903  for (uint32_t j = 0; j < stream_input_desc_count; j++)
2904  {
2905  avdecc_lib::stream_input_descriptor * instream = configuration->get_stream_input_desc_by_index(j);
2906  instream->send_get_rx_state_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id);
2907  }
2908 
2909  size_t stream_output_desc_count = configuration->stream_output_desc_count();
2910 
2911  for (uint32_t j = 0; j < stream_output_desc_count; j++)
2912  {
2913  // Only wait when issuing the last packet
2914  const bool last_command = (i == controller_obj->get_end_station_count() - 1) &&
2915  (j == stream_output_desc_count - 1);
2916  if (last_command)
2917  sys->set_wait_for_next_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id);
2918  avdecc_lib::stream_output_descriptor * outstream = configuration->get_stream_output_desc_by_index(j);
2919  outstream->send_get_tx_state_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id);
2920  if (last_command)
2921  sys->get_last_resp_status();
2922  }
2923  }
2924 
2925  for (uint32_t in_index = 0; in_index < controller_obj->get_end_station_count(); in_index++)
2926  {
2927  avdecc_lib::end_station * in_end_station = controller_obj->get_end_station_by_index(in_index);
2928  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor * in_entity;
2929  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * in_descriptor;
2930  if (get_current_entity_and_descriptor(in_end_station, &in_entity, &in_descriptor))
2931  continue;
2932 
2933  size_t stream_input_desc_count = in_descriptor->stream_input_desc_count();
2934  for (uint32_t in_stream_index = 0; in_stream_index < stream_input_desc_count; in_stream_index++)
2935  {
2936  avdecc_lib::stream_input_descriptor * instream = in_descriptor->get_stream_input_desc_by_index(in_stream_index);
2937  avdecc_lib::stream_input_get_rx_state_response * stream_input_resp_ref = instream->get_stream_input_get_rx_state_response();
2938  if (!stream_input_resp_ref->get_rx_state_connection_count())
2939  {
2940  delete stream_input_resp_ref;
2941  continue;
2942  }
2943  delete stream_input_resp_ref;
2944 
2945  for (uint32_t out_index = 0; out_index < controller_obj->get_end_station_count(); out_index++)
2946  {
2947  avdecc_lib::end_station * out_end_station = controller_obj->get_end_station_by_index(out_index);
2948  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor * out_entity;
2949  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * out_descriptor;
2950  if (get_current_entity_and_descriptor(out_end_station, &out_entity, &out_descriptor))
2951  continue;
2952 
2953  size_t stream_output_desc_count = out_descriptor->stream_output_desc_count();
2954  for (uint32_t out_stream_index = 0; out_stream_index < stream_output_desc_count; out_stream_index++)
2955  {
2956  avdecc_lib::stream_input_get_rx_state_response * stream_input_resp_ref = instream->get_stream_input_get_rx_state_response();
2957  avdecc_lib::stream_output_descriptor * outstream = out_descriptor->get_stream_output_desc_by_index(out_stream_index);
2958  avdecc_lib::stream_output_get_tx_state_response * stream_output_resp_ref = outstream->get_stream_output_get_tx_state_response();
2959  if (!stream_output_resp_ref->get_tx_state_connection_count() ||
2960  (stream_input_resp_ref->get_rx_state_stream_id() != stream_output_resp_ref->get_tx_state_stream_id()))
2961  {
2962  delete stream_input_resp_ref;
2963  delete stream_output_resp_ref;
2964 
2965  continue;
2966  }
2967 
2968  atomic_cout << "0x" << std::setw(16) << std::hex << std::setfill('0') << out_end_station->entity_id()
2969  << "[" << in_stream_index << "] -> "
2970  << "0x" << std::setw(16) << std::hex << std::setfill('0') << in_end_station->entity_id()
2971  << "[" << out_stream_index << "]" << std::endl;
2972 
2973  delete stream_input_resp_ref;
2974  delete stream_output_resp_ref;
2975  }
2976  }
2977  }
2978  }
2979  return 0;
2980 }

3586  std::string new_stream_format = args[2]->get_value_str();
3587 
3588  uint16_t desc_type_value = avdecc_lib::utility::aem_desc_name_to_value(desc_name.c_str());
3589  unsigned int stream_format_index = 0;
3590  uint64_t stream_format_value = 0;
3591  std::string stream_format;
3592 
3593  if (new_stream_format.at(0) == 'I')
3594  {
3595  std::string stream_format_substring = new_stream_format.substr(20);
3596  stream_format_value = avdecc_lib::utility::ieee1722_format_name_to_value(("IEC..." + stream_format_substring).c_str());
3597  }
3598  else
3599  {
3600  stream_format_index = atoi(new_stream_format.c_str());
3601  stream_format_value = avdecc_lib::utility::ieee1722_format_index_to_value(stream_format_index);
3602  }
3603 
3604  avdecc_lib::end_station * end_station;
3605  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor * entity;
3606  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * configuration;
3607  if (get_current_end_station_entity_and_descriptor(&end_station, &entity, &configuration))
3608  return 0;
3609 
3610  if (desc_type_value == avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_STREAM_INPUT)
3611  {
3612  intptr_t cmd_notification_id = get_next_notification_id();
3613  sys->set_wait_for_next_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id);
3614  avdecc_lib::stream_input_descriptor * stream_input_desc_ref = configuration->get_stream_input_desc_by_index(desc_index);
3615  stream_input_desc_ref->send_set_stream_format_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id, stream_format_value);
3616  int status = sys->get_last_resp_status();
3617 
3618  if (status == avdecc_lib::AEM_STATUS_SUCCESS)
3619  {
3620  avdecc_lib::stream_input_descriptor_response * stream_input_resp_ref = stream_input_desc_ref->get_stream_input_response();
3621  stream_format = stream_input_resp_ref->current_format_name();
3622  if (stream_format == "UNKNOWN")
3623  {
3624  atomic_cout << "Stream format: 0x" << std::hex << stream_input_resp_ref->current_format_value() << std::endl;
3625  }
3626  else
3627  {
3628  atomic_cout << "Stream format: " << stream_format << std::endl;
3629  }
3630  delete stream_input_resp_ref;
3631  }
3632  }
3633  else if (desc_type_value == avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_STREAM_OUTPUT)
3634  {
3635  intptr_t cmd_notification_id = get_next_notification_id();
3636  sys->set_wait_for_next_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id);
3637  avdecc_lib::stream_output_descriptor * stream_output_desc_ref = configuration->get_stream_output_desc_by_index(desc_index);
3638  stream_output_desc_ref->send_set_stream_format_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id, stream_format_value);
3639  int status = sys->get_last_resp_status();
3640 
3641  if (status == avdecc_lib::AEM_STATUS_SUCCESS)
3642  {
3643  avdecc_lib::stream_output_descriptor_response * stream_output_resp_ref = stream_output_desc_ref->get_stream_output_response();
3644  stream_format = stream_output_resp_ref->current_format_name();
3645  if (stream_format == "UNKNOWN")
3646  {
3647  atomic_cout << "Stream format: 0x" << std::hex << stream_output_resp_ref->current_format_value() << std::endl;
3648  }
3649  else
3650  {
3651  atomic_cout << "Stream format: " << stream_format << std::endl;
3652  }
3653  delete stream_output_resp_ref;
3654  }
3655  }
3656  else
3657  {
3658  atomic_cout << "cmd_set_stream_format error" << std::endl;

3983 int cmd_line::cmd_display_desc_name(avdecc_lib::descriptor_base * desc, uint16_t name_index, bool is_entity)
3984 {
3985  uint8_t * name;
3986  avdecc_lib::end_station * end_station;
3987  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor * entity;
3988  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * configuration;
3989 
3990  if (get_current_end_station_entity_and_descriptor(&end_station, &entity,
3991  &configuration))
3992  return 0;
3993 
3994  if (is_entity == true)
3995  {
3996  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor_response * entity_resp_ref = entity->get_entity_response();
3997  if (name_index == 0)
3998  {
3999  name = entity_resp_ref->entity_name();
4000  }
4001  else
4002  {
4003  name = entity_resp_ref->group_name();
4004  }
4005  delete entity_resp_ref;
4006  }
4007  else
4008  {
4009  avdecc_lib::descriptor_response_base * desc_resp_base = desc->get_descriptor_response();
4010  name = desc_resp_base->object_name();
4011  delete desc_resp_base;
4012  }
4013 
4014  if (!name)
4015  {
4016  atomic_cout << "cmd_set_name() failed" << std::endl;
4017  }
4018  else
4019  {
4020  atomic_cout << "Descriptor " << avdecc_lib::utility::aem_desc_value_to_name(desc->descriptor_type()) << "." << desc->descriptor_index() << " name at index " << name_index << ": " << std::dec << name << std::endl;
4021  }
4022 
4023  return 0;
4024 }

4026 int cmd_line::cmd_get_name(int total_matched, std::vector<cli_argument *> args)
4027 {

4030  uint16_t desc_index = args[1]->get_value_int();
4031 
4032  uint16_t desc_type = avdecc_lib::utility::aem_desc_name_to_value(desc_name.c_str());
4033 
4034  avdecc_lib::end_station * end_station;
4035  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor * entity;
4036  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * configuration;
4037  avdecc_lib::descriptor_base * desc_base = NULL;

4040  &configuration))
4041  return 0;
4042 
4043  if (desc_type == avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_ENTITY)
4044  {
4045  desc_base = dynamic_cast<avdecc_lib::descriptor_base *>(entity);
4046  }
4047  else if (desc_type == avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_CONFIGURATION)
4048  {
4049  desc_base = dynamic_cast<avdecc_lib::descriptor_base *>(configuration);
4050  }
4051  else
4052  {
4053  desc_base = configuration->lookup_desc(desc_type, desc_index);
4054  }
4055 
4056  if (!desc_base)
4057  {

4071  uint8_t * name = get_name_resp->get_name();

4488  cmd_notification_id = get_next_notification_id();
4489  sys->set_wait_for_next_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id);
4490  avdecc_lib::stream_input_descriptor * stream_input_desc_ref = configuration->get_stream_input_desc_by_index(desc_index);
4491  stream_input_desc_ref->send_start_streaming_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id);
4492  sys->get_last_resp_status();
4493  }
4494  else if (desc_type_value == avdecc_lib::AEM_DESC_STREAM_OUTPUT)
4495  {
4496  cmd_notification_id = get_next_notification_id();
4497  sys->set_wait_for_next_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id);
4498  avdecc_lib::stream_output_descriptor * stream_output_desc_ref = configuration->get_stream_output_desc_by_index(desc_index);
4499  stream_output_desc_ref->send_start_streaming_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id);
4500  sys->get_last_resp_status();
4501  }

4503  {
4504  atomic_cout << "cmd_start_streaming error" << std::endl;
4505  }

4548 int cmd_line::cmd_firmware_upgrade(int total_matched, std::vector<cli_argument *> args)
4549 {
4550  std::string image_file_path = args[0]->get_value_str();
4551  std::ifstream is(image_file_path, std::ios::in | std::ios::binary);
4552 
4553  if (is.is_open())
4554  {
4555  avdecc_lib::end_station * end_station;
4556  avdecc_lib::entity_descriptor * entity;
4557  avdecc_lib::configuration_descriptor * configuration;
4558  if (get_current_end_station_entity_and_descriptor(&end_station, &entity, &configuration))
4559  return 0;
4560 
4561  intptr_t cmd_notification_id = get_next_notification_id();
4562  sys->set_wait_for_next_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id);
4563  avdecc_lib::memory_object_descriptor * memory_object_desc_ref = configuration->get_memory_object_desc_by_index(0);
4564  atomic_cout << "Erasing image..." << std::endl;
4565  memory_object_desc_ref->start_operation_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id, 3);
4566  int status = sys->get_last_resp_status();
4567 
4568  if (status)
4569  {
4570  atomic_cout << "Error: Erase failed." << std::endl;
4571  return 0;
4572  }
4573  else
4574  {
4575  atomic_cout << "Succesfully erased." << std::endl;
4576  }
4577 
4578  std::streampos current = 0;
4579  char buffer[256];
4580  is.seekg(0, std::ios::beg);
4581 
4582  is.read(buffer, 256);
4583 
4584  while (is.gcount())
4585  {
4586  sys->set_wait_for_next_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id);
4587  end_station->send_aecp_address_access_cmd((void *)cmd_notification_id,
4588  1,
4589  (unsigned int)is.gcount(),
4590  int(current),
4591  (uint8_t *)buffer);
4592  status = sys->get_last_resp_status();
4593  if (status)
4594  {
4595  atomic_cout << "Error: Could not write TLV at address " << current << std::endl;
4596  return 0;
4597  }
4598  current += 256;
4599  is.read(buffer, 256);
4600  }
4601 
4602  is.close();
4603 
4604  atomic_cout << "Successfully upgraded image." << std::endl;
4605 
4606  std::string yn;
4607  atomic_cout << "Do you want to reboot the device? [y/n]: ";
4608  std::cin >> yn;
4609 
4610  while (1)
4611  {
4612  if (yn == "Y" || yn == "y")
4613  {
4614  cmd_reboot(0, std::vector<cli_argument *>());
4615  break;
4616  }
4617  else if (yn == "N" || yn == "n")
4618  {
4619  break;
4620  }
4621  else
4622  {
4623  atomic_cout << "Please answer \"y\" or \"n\": ";
4624  std::cin >> yn;
4625  }
4626  }
4627  }
4628  else
4629  {
4630  atomic_cout << "Error: Unable to open upgrade image at " << image_file_path << std::endl;
4631  return 0;
4632  }
4633 
4634  return 0;
4635 }

4690 bool cmd_line::is_setting_valid(uint32_t end_station, uint16_t entity, uint16_t config)
4691 {
4692  bool is_setting_valid = (end_station < controller_obj->get_end_station_count()) &&
4693  (entity < controller_obj->get_end_station_by_index(end_station)->entity_desc_count()) &&
4694  (config < controller_obj->get_end_station_by_index(end_station)->get_entity_desc_by_index(entity)->config_desc_count());
4695 
4696  return is_setting_valid;
4697 }

4699 bool cmd_line::get_end_station_index(std::string arg, uint32_t & end_station_index) const
4700 {
4701  uint64_t entity_entity_id = 0;
4702  const char * str = arg.c_str();
4703  char * end;
4704 
4705  // Try treating the argument as a Entity ID
4706  entity_entity_id = strtoull(str, &end, 16);
4707  if (end != str)
4708  {
4709  bool found = controller_obj->is_end_station_found_by_entity_id(entity_entity_id, end_station_index);
4710  if (found)
4711  return true;
4712  }
4713 
4714  // Not a valid Entity ID, so assume it is an index
4715  end_station_index = strtoul(str, &end, 10);
4716  if (end != str)
4717  return true;
4718 
4719  return false;
4720 }
